cff-version: 1.2.0

# ── Project identity ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

title: "Permi"

abstract: >
  Permi is an open-source, AI-powered static vulnerability scanner for
  developers and SMBs. It detects common security vulnerabilities — including
  SQL injection, cross-site scripting, hardcoded secrets, and insecure
  practices — using a regex-based rule engine, and applies a large language
  model filter to reduce false positives. Permi includes vulnerability rules
  specific to the Nigerian development context, including USSD gateway
  misconfigurations and local payment gateway credential exposure. It runs
  entirely locally with no cloud backend required, storing results in a local
  SQLite database. Permi is distributed as a Python CLI package via PyPI and
  is designed to be accessible to developers in emerging markets who are
  underserved by expensive, enterprise-focused security tooling.

